Notes: pohaki (x2) sic in citation? (from the net) Pouhaki Flagpole Although not always carved the Pou-haki is used primarily during Tangi funerals. During the tangi the flag is flown at half mast while the Tupapaku deceased is on the Marae. The Pouhaki is also used during major Hui conferences/meetings...
